    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing NGAP UE Context Release Complete message in successful UE release handling\n\n### Summary\nWhen processing NGAP UE Context Release Command messages, the gNB was not sending the required NGAP UE Context Release Complete message back to the AMF in successful cases. This caused the AMF to wait indefinitely for the completion message, leading to stalled UE context cleanup procedures.\n\nThe issue was in `rrc_gNB_process_NGAP_UE_CONTEXT_RELEASE_COMMAND()` where the function would send an RRC Release to the UE but fail to notify the AMF of completion in the success path. The completion message was only sent in error cases.\n\nThis fix ensures that `rrc_gNB_send_NGAP_UE_CONTEXT_RELEASE_COMPLETE()` is called in both error and success cases, maintaining proper NGAP protocol flow.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/rrc_gNB_NGAP.c`: Added call to `rrc_gNB_send_NGAP_UE_CONTEXT_RELEASE_COMPLETE()` in the success path of `rrc_gNB_process_NGAP_UE_CONTEXT_RELEASE_COMMAND()`.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Establish a UE connection to the gNB\n2. Trigger an AMF-initiated UE context release by sending a NGAP UE Context Release Command\n3. Observe that the gNB sends RRC Release to UE but does not send NGAP UE Context Release Complete to AMF\n4. AMF will timeout waiting for the completion message\n5. UE context remains in inconsistent state between gNB and AMF\n\nWith this fix, the NGAP UE Context Release Complete message is properly sent to the AMF after processing the release command, allowing normal protocol flow to continue.\n"
}